e some organizational clarity. I'm reconsidering what counts as a real omission versus acceptable simplification. Item 3 about the default behavior when `extendedStringConvertors` isn't set is already implied by the empty default shown in the table, so that's not worth flagging. Item 2 about adding annotations to setters is demonstrated in the code example itself, so that's fine too. The actual gaps I should focus on are the missing `parseFailedMessageId` hint and the fact that the source has 9 sections but the knowledge file only captures 1.\n\nNow I need to verify the V2 findings more carefully, particularly checking whether the `trimPolicy` description accurately reflects what the source says about how `String#trim()` handles different whitespace characters. リム機能を持つカスタムコンバータを作成すること。Javaの標準String#trim()メソッドを使用して、文字列の前後にある'\\u0020'以下のコード値を持つ文字（半角スペース、タブ、改行、null文字など）を削除する。'\\u0020'より大きいコード値の文字はトリムされないため、全角スペースなどをトリムする必要がある場合は、アクション内で対応するか、全角スペースのトリム機能を持つカスタムコンバータを作成して対応する。\n\nThe knowledge file simplifies some terminology and omits specific character examples, but these are minor. I'm now reviewing whether all my findings are worth reporting. The slash removal use case for `extendedStringConvertors` is actually useful context for developers deciding when to use the feature, so I'll keep that. The missing `private String date;` field is just a minor code detail since the annotated setter is what matters. The section consolidation and missing `parseFailedMessageId` hint are both minor structural omissions worth noting.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":22250,"cache_read_input_tokens":29873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":22250,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"55ce5526-82f8-44d4-ab03-6fb8aa47f81e","uuid":"3068681e-648e-4930-b7b8-6f0968b03b5c"}
